Title: Object: Moses and Aaron before Pharoah
Series: Dalziels' Bible Gallery
Description: Moses in Egypt, standing at left in a hall, addressing bystanders around him, pleading for the freedom of the Israelites; the Pharoah seated behind him on his throne under a canope on top of stairs, attended by servants; a group of men worshipping an idol in foreground; snakes on the stairs; after Edward John Poynter. 1863 Wood-engraving, heightened with Chinese white
Curator's comments: For Dalziels' Bible Gallery, see 1996,1104.4. The uncut woodblock is in the Victoria and Albert Museum.
